Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,,0000,0000,0000,,DETECTIVE CONAN EPISODE 1060 "Okino \NYoko and the Locked Attic (Part Two)"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,[op]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,[ed]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:00.00,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,[eyecatch]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.06,0:00:06.19,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Okino Yoko-san came to the detective agency \Nto ask the old man about a case.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.86,0:00:12.40,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,While location scouting, she visited a \Nvilla where a woman went missing
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.40,0:00:16.32,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and wanted him to solve the murder \Nthat happened while she was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.99,0:00:24.42,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,However, the old man's been holed \Nup in the bathroom this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.87,0:00:26.79,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is he doing in there?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.11,0:00:33.05,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of person was \Nthe wife who went missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.19,0:00:36.55,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You mean producer Heijima's sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.16,0:00:42.31,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}This woman in sunglasses on the left \Nis Heijima-san's sister Baba Hoka-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.97,0:00:41.85,Hoka,SIGN LEFT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(370,370)}Baba Hoka \NNukiyasu's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.97,0:00:41.85,Himi,SIGN RIGHT,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(370,370)}Baba Himi (43) \NFugo's Wife
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.46,0:00:44.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Did she often wear sunglasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:45.88,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.88,0:00:50.56,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Heijima-san said before she went missing \Nshe'd gotten into them and often wore a pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.61,0:00:54.97,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Fugo-san's first love was Hoka-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.97,0:00:57.57,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and she and Himi-san were best friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.89,0:00:59.70,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.70,0:01:07.58,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Which means if her husband Nukiyasu-san \Nis the reason Hoka-san went missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.77,0:01:13.09,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,then all three of them had \Nmotive to kill Nukiyasu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.51,0:01:22.30,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Mysterious clouds block your field of view!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.30,0:01:24.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Clear them away with deductive \Nreasoning and the sky sparkles!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.18,0:01:27.97,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Expose the truth hidden away in the \Ncode expressed through playing cards!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.97,0:01:29.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Always determining the one truth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.80,0:01:31.67,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,with the body of a child \Nand the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.67,0:01:34.11,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,his name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.96,0:03:21.97,DCEpTitle,EPTITLE,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(402,1)}Okino Yoko and the Locked Attic \N(Part Two)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.62,0:03:20.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,"Okino Yoko and the Locked Attic, Part Two!"
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.14,0:03:25.97,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,So was there anything else \Nthat caught your attention?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.27,0:03:30.60,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The pine trees around the villa, maybe?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.76,0:03:32.73,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What about the pine trees?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.17,0:03:36.48,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Heijima-san said something \Nwhen we arrived at the villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.69,0:03:40.53,Heijima,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(370,370)}Heijima Wanya (39) \NTV Producer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.06,0:03:41.82,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}There were 17 pine trees when he visited \Nthree years ago, and now there were only 16.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.26,0:03:43.81,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}When we asked Nukiyasu-san about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.45,0:03:45.91,Nukiyasu,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(370,370)}Baba Nukiyasu (46) \NEldest Son of the Baba Family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.81,0:03:48.49,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}he said he transplanted it to his home in \NTokyo because it was a nicely shaped tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.67,0:03:53.05,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,It's incredible that he remembered \Nhow many pine trees there were.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.05,0:03:55.76,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He's got a very good memory.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.76,0:04:00.51,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He can list off the birthdays of TV staff \Nand talent after hearing them only once.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.89,0:04:03.01,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that reminds me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.33,0:04:07.74,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}When we were talking about that pine \Ntree, Fugo-san told Heijima-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.30,0:04:10.02,Fugo,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(370,1)}Baba Fugo (44) \NSecond Son of the Baba Family
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.74,0:04:10.02,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}"You're the true ace!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.44,0:04:12.52,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,What did he mean by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.76,0:04:15.30,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to ask him about it later,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:18.52,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but then the murder happened, and it didn't \Nseem like the right time to ask anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.81,0:04:22.05,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Just to be sure,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.05,0:04:30.24,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,the trail of blood that ended around the \Ncorner didn't end near the attic entrance, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.43,0:04:31.52,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.52,0:04:36.00,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,The entrance was on the ceiling a short \Ndistance away and around another corner,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.30,0:04:39.30,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and the attic stairs had been stored away.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.74,0:04:44.65,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You tried calling Nukiyasu-san's phone \Nnumerous times while looking for him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.65,0:04:46.91,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, his younger brother did.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.91,0:04:51.27,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He borrowed his wife's phone since \Nhis own was nearly out of batteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.74,0:04:55.65,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone really did sympathetically \Nengage in the search for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.65,0:04:58.96,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, Heijima-san, who was \Npaired with me, did as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.96,0:05:02.78,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,but the younger brother and his wife also \Ncalled out for him while looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.78,0:05:10.28,DCNote,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Mori Detective Agency
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.46,0:05:11.69,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.69,0:05:13.54,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Something terrible is bound to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.07,0:05:18.54,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I call or message Ran about \Nit, Yoko-chan would probably find out...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.80,0:05:21.87,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,that I need toilet paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:24.30,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Since it's come to this,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.30,0:05:29.80,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to rely on that sort of clever \Nbut insolent kid with the glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:36.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The old man sent me a message?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.92,0:05:42.61,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.23,0:05:48.36,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro-no-ojisan just sent me this message.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.09,0:05:53.87,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.25,0:05:57.37,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't Mori-san in the bathroom right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.40,0:06:03.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,They're starting to look \Nlike mahjong tiles to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.69,0:06:08.09,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What? Ran-chan, you know how to play mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.32,0:06:11.85,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I got into it for \Na little while before.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.37,0:06:13.70,DCItalic,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,Mahjong...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.81,0:06:16.60,DCItalic,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.90,0:06:18.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.40,0:06:24.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But why would he bother sending \Na coded message to tell me that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.16,0:06:27.38,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He could just shout for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.01,0:06:32.75,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Ah-ha. I see how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.80,0:06:34.98,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.61,0:06:37.50,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't these situations similar?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.02,0:06:40.71,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's trapped inside a certain \Nlocation and can't come out,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.26,0:06:43.69,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,so he has to send a coded message.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.35,0:06:46.14,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The reason for that and \Ncontents of the message are...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.08,0:06:52.72,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.07,0:06:58.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Nukiyasu-san didn't call or send a \Ntext but a picture of these playing cards.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.20,0:07:01.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He had no idea his code \Nwould be used against him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.47,0:07:05.73,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and keep him trapped inside the attic.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.33,0:07:14.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What? You deciphered the playing card code?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.51,0:07:16.27,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Is that true, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.27,0:07:17.38,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.38,0:07:22.04,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,This code using numbers \Nand kanji Kogoro-no-ojisan
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.46,0:07:26.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,just sent me from inside the \Nbathroom provided a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.72,0:07:29.01,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You deciphered that code, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.31,0:07:33.51,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Even a child could figure it out \Nwith a little bit of thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.75,0:07:37.76,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But why did he send you that code?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.16,0:07:43.28,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Probably because he wanted to request \Nsomething from inside the bathroom
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:45.27,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,without the object of his \Nadoration finding out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.92,0:07:53.78,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Just as Nukiyasu-san sent his \Nbrother that playing card code
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.14,0:07:59.75,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,while he was hiding in the attic after \Nbeing shot in the back with a crossbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.34,0:08:01.76,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.76,0:08:05.42,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,So, what's the solution \Nto the playing card code?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.16,0:08:09.00,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,You convert the symbols \Non the cards into English
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.00,0:08:15.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and string together the English letters \Nindicated by the number on the card.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.70,0:08:19.80,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the first card on \Nthe top left is the ace of hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.80,0:08:26.61,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the first letter of heart \Nspelled H-E-A-R-T is H.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.29,0:08:30.25,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The second card is the \Ntwo of hearts, so it's E.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.25,0:08:32.52,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The third card is the two of clubs,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.52,0:08:37.37,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and club is spelled C-L-U-B, so it's L.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.55,0:08:39.94,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you can speak English?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.94,0:08:42.37,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I know. Isn't it surprising?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.59,0:08:45.33,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The fourth card is the two of spades,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.33,0:08:49.88,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and spade is spelled S-P-A-D-E, so it's P.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.76,0:08:55.95,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,If you string together the first four \Ncards on the top left, you get H-E-L-P.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.24,0:08:59.64,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,He's asking for help.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.55,0:09:02.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.82,0:09:05.14,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun, you really are a genius.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.66,0:09:08.91,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,You might even overtake Dad before long.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.67,0:09:12.65,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,It's not impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.04,0:09:13.95,DCItalic,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Crap.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.52,0:09:19.91,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,But I forgot how to spell diamond, \Nso I don't think I can read the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.26,0:09:26.87,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Diamond is spelled D-I-A-M-O-N-D.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.87,0:09:28.42,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He really is just a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.95,0:09:33.42,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But if you read the second pile of \Ncards according to that principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.73,0:09:37.72,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,you have the three of spades, the five \Nof hearts, the five of hearts again,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.72,0:09:41.18,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,the two of diamonds, and the ace of clubs,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.69,0:09:44.59,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,which spells A-T-T-I-C.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.38,0:09:46.73,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.73,0:09:53.07,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows? "Attack" as in \Nassault is spelled A-T-T-A-C-K.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.56,0:09:53.07,Assault,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,(Assault)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.26,0:09:57.45,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,It's "attic," the room beneath \Nthe roof of a building.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.77,0:10:01.58,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right. Both "help" and \N"attic" are English words.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.58,0:10:08.50,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Then the piles of six and two of diamonds \Nand two of diamonds, four of hearts,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.50,0:10:13.84,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and three of clubs after \Nthat spell N-I and I-R-U.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.19,0:10:18.38,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Those are read normally as \Nromaji as "ni" and "iru."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:20.72,Romaji,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(460,335)}NI = in \NIRU = to be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.38,0:10:20.69,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,All together, they spell, "I'm in the attic."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.69,0:10:25.60,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, he's saying, \N"Help me, I'm in the attic."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.01,0:10:29.79,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,He only had 16 letters of \Nthe alphabet to work with,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.79,0:10:33.24,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,so he probably had no choice but \Nto mix English and Japanese.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.24,0:10:34.61,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.92,0:10:41.87,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,But the bottom row of cards seems to \Nbe entirely Japanese written as romaji.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.38,0:10:44.83,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see. That would be...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.46,0:10:50.12,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.36,0:10:58.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.84,0:11:00.01,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Himi?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.78,0:11:06.61,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't Himi-san Fugo-san's wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.61,0:11:09.41,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But she was in a wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.90,0:11:13.27,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,You can fire a crossbow from a wheelchair.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.88,0:11:18.30,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,And if you set the crossbow in your \Nlap and cover it with a blanket,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.30,0:11:22.78,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,you can approach your victim \Nwithout them suspecting a thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.24,0:11:28.06,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, this code says, "My \Nbrother, your wife is the culprit,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.06,0:11:34.54,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,so come up to the attic and \Nhelp me without her noticing."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.93,0:11:39.89,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Himi-san probably asked to meet Nukiyasu-san \Nout into the hallway at midnight
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.89,0:11:41.64,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and pointed the crossbow at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.64,0:11:46.56,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,She fired a bolt into his back \Nwhile he was running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.25,0:11:49.58,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,However, he escaped before \Nshe could finish him off,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.58,0:11:51.90,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and though she went after \Nhim in her wheelchair,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.90,0:11:56.57,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,she realized you were following \NNukiyasu-san's blood trail.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.34,0:12:01.42,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,To keep you from following \Nthe trail any farther,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.42,0:12:05.45,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Himi-san laid the blanket under \Nthe wheelchair's footrests,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.68,0:12:07.66,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,held it down with her feet,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.66,0:12:12.71,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and followed Nukiyasu-san while \Nwiping up the blood in the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.13,0:12:19.71,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Th-That's why the trail suddenly \Nstopped when I turned the corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:25.72,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, so you couldn't stop her \Nfrom trying to kill Nukiyasu-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.99,0:12:32.23,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,But the time she spent doing that \Nallowed him to escape into the attic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.41,0:12:37.73,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,After losing sight of Nukiyasu-san, \NHimi-san gathered with everyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.73,0:12:42.24,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,in front of the bathroom as \Nthough nothing had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.11,0:12:49.17,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,B-But after that Himi-san did her best \Nto search for Nukiyasu-san, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.17,0:12:52.04,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,She even shouted his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.43,0:12:55.25,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe she was acting.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.25,0:12:58.58,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,She wasn't looking for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.58,0:12:59.29,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:01.42,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,She was threatening him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.91,0:13:04.42,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,"Come on down if you can."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.70,0:13:09.42,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,"I'll kill you with this \Ncrossbow as soon as you do."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.10,0:13:11.97,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,B-But...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.97,0:13:17.44,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean Himi-san knew \NNukiyasu-san was hiding in the attic?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.63,0:13:18.84,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.84,0:13:24.53,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Since Nukiyasu-san's blood trail stopped \Ndirectly beneath the attic entrance,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.53,0:13:26.70,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,she could easily imagine what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.04,0:13:30.80,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then shouldn't he have called \Nhis brother Fugo-san normally
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.80,0:13:34.84,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,instead of sending the playing card code?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.84,0:13:36.32,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.32,0:13:40.46,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,He could've said, "Your wife shot me \Nwith a crossbow. Have her arrested."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.69,0:13:45.19,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,But Himi-san still had \Nthe crossbow in her lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.19,0:13:49.84,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,If he said the wrong thing, \NHimi-san might've killed him, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.84,0:13:51.21,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.21,0:13:54.79,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why he tried to secretly \Nconvey the message with a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.79,0:13:58.98,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Then he might've survived if \NFugo-san had deciphered the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.26,0:14:04.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I think he knew and \Nwas pretending he didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.49,0:14:07.91,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, now. What's going on out there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.24,0:14:11.80,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I sent him a coded message explaining \Nthat I'm out of toilet paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.80,0:14:13.49,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,so why isn't he responding?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.84,0:14:18.40,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Was that mahjong code too difficult \Nfor a kid to understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.40,0:14:23.63,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,No, he once made some excellent \Nplays while sitting on my lap.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.21,0:14:26.01,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way he doesn't know what it means.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.44,0:14:30.29,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Not only that, but I've been hearing the voice \Nof Wakita from Iroha Sushi for a while, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.29,0:14:33.76,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,If he finds out about this...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:36.25,DCItalic,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive, Master Kogoro.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.25,0:14:39.60,DCItalic,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,You're out of paper, but \Nyour wits are outstanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.31,0:14:44.52,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,I have to do whatever it \Ntakes to prevent that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.77,0:14:45.51,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.51,0:14:48.26,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He knew but pretended he didn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.26,0:14:49.70,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why would he do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.70,0:14:52.66,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,To protect his own wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.99,0:14:53.62,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.09,0:14:57.29,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,But isn't that just your guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.80,0:15:02.71,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Nukiyasu-san called his brother "ace," right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.23,0:15:05.46,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Since ace is the number one,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.46,0:15:09.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,if you rearrange the first letters \Nof spade, heart, club, and diamond,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.60,0:15:12.72,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,you get SDHC.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.01,0:15:17.72,DCMain,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,SDHC Card
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.47,0:15:17.94,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Add the word "card" to the end of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.94,0:15:22.18,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and it means a memory card with \Ngreater capacity than an SD card.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.85,0:15:26.86,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,That's why he called his brother,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.86,0:15:30.24,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,who'd always been on the big side, ace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.49,0:15:32.45,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.45,0:15:36.49,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm surprised you knew \Nabout SDHC cards though.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.85,0:15:39.50,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi-niichan told me about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.73,0:15:43.27,DCItalic,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinichi's been teaching this \Nkid tricky concepts again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.44,0:15:48.51,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But his brother said he didn't \Nknow why he called him that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.73,0:15:52.01,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,No, he probably knew what it meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.45,0:15:54.77,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,He apparently even told the producer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.77,0:15:58.26,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,with a good memory that he was the real ace.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.52,0:15:59.51,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.51,0:16:00.74,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.74,0:16:03.77,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,And when his brother was hiding in the attic,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.97,0:16:06.92,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Fugo-san claimed his phone \Nwas running out of batteries,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.92,0:16:11.97,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and deliberately used his wife the \Nculprit's phone to call his brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.58,0:16:14.69,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why did he use his wife's phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.69,0:16:20.81,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,If you received a call from \Nthe person trying to kill you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.81,0:16:21.90,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,what would you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.90,0:16:23.49,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.49,0:16:25.67,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,What if you were hiding somewhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.91,0:16:29.47,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally I'd turn of my phone \Nso it wouldn't make a sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.90,0:16:32.60,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.60,0:16:39.31,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,By doing that, Fugo-san forced \NNukiyasu-san to turn off his phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.48,0:16:43.96,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,completely cutting him off from the outside \Nand trapping him alone in the attic
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.96,0:16:50.32,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,so he'd die waiting for his brother's \Nhelp that would never come.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.78,0:16:54.78,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,But why would he kill his own \Nbrother to protect his wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.78,0:16:59.08,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Fugo-san probably resented his brother, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.32,0:17:03.02,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,My gut's telling me Nukiyasu-san's wife
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.02,0:17:06.74,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and Fugo-san's first love, Hoka-san,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.00,0:17:11.76,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,is dead and buried somewhere near the villa.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.18,0:17:13.38,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.60,0:17:16.13,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,In the photo of Hoka-san we saw earlier,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.67,0:17:19.73,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,the other four are wearing \Nbreezy summer clothes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.73,0:17:23.38,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,but Fuko-san alone is wearing \Nlong sleeves and sunglasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.38,0:17:28.39,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,If she started wearing sunglasses a \Nfew years before she went missing,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.65,0:17:34.65,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,then it's safe to assume her husband \Nhad started abusing her since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.05,0:17:36.28,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Abuse?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.43,0:17:38.89,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,So she was wearing long \Nsleeves and sunglasses
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.89,0:17:43.29,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,to hide the bruises left by her \Nhusband hitting and kicking her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.65,0:17:47.61,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,It's also a lie that two years ago, her husband \NNukiyasu-san had something come up
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.61,0:17:52.78,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and Hoka-san headed to the villa alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.78,0:17:57.02,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,I'm betting he actually killed her \Nwhen he took the abuse too far
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.02,0:17:58.80,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,at the villa and hid the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.20,0:18:02.75,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Then he claimed his wife went missing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.75,0:18:07.31,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,when he arrived later with \Nhis brother and his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.53,0:18:11.06,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,It's suspicious that he transplanted \None of the pine trees
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.06,0:18:14.68,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,around the villa to his \Nhome three years ago, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.68,0:18:15.82,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.25,0:18:21.57,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,You have to dig all the way down \Nto the roots to transplant a tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.12,0:18:27.46,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,If he stopped the workers from filling it in by \Nclaiming he wanted to plant a new tree in the hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.46,0:18:31.10,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,then he could've secretly buried his \Nwife's body at the bottom of the hole,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.10,0:18:35.79,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and then said he decided not to plant a new \Ntree after all and have them fill it in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.79,0:18:40.47,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,That would allow him to hide the body deep \Nunderground where no one could find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.21,0:18:48.23,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit Himi-san probably suspected \NNukiyasu-san had killed Hoka-san
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.52,0:18:53.23,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and interrogated him while \Npointing the crossbow at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.81,0:18:57.24,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,"Where's my friend's body?"
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.66,0:19:00.74,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,"You killed her, didn't you?"
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.01,0:19:02.30,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.30,0:19:05.80,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why Nukiyasu-san \Ncouldn't call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.64,0:19:07.90,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.90,0:19:10.85,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,If the police showed up, \NHimi-san would be arrested,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.37,0:19:14.93,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,but if she told them the woman \Nwho went missing two years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.93,0:19:17.38,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,had been killed by her husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.92,0:19:20.64,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,they might dig up the area around the villa
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.64,0:19:24.81,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and find his wife's body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.45,0:19:29.64,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, Nukiyasu-san sent \Nthat playing card code to his brother
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.64,0:19:31.95,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,hoping to make it through the crisis
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.95,0:19:35.19,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and flee to someplace far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.59,0:19:38.94,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Whoops, I got carried away running my mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.60,0:19:45.67,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,But all of this is just the \Nkid's and my deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.67,0:19:47.99,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have any proof.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.61,0:19:53.16,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,But if you tell the police, have them \Ndig up the spot where the pine tree was,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.16,0:19:55.88,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,and they find Hoka-san's body,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:20:00.51,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,then Himi-san might admit her guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.36,0:20:02.29,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.29,0:20:05.78,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll start by talking to \Nthe producer Heijima-san
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.78,0:20:07.74,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,and have a conversation with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.19,0:20:09.77,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.03,0:20:13.77,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, you solved the case without Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.05,0:20:16.76,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,Wakita-san, you're an incredible detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.76,0:20:19.78,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Not as good as my master.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.11,0:20:25.16,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, what \Nwas dad's code about?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.36,0:20:28.58,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Like you said, it was mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.25,0:20:34.81,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The top row is one tile short of \Na hand called "thirteen orphans."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.81,0:20:38.34,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The bottom row is one tile short \Nof a hand called "nine gates."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.82,0:20:44.03,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,The "thirteen orphans" hand is \Nmissing a north or "pei" tile,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.03,0:20:49.60,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,and the "nine gates" hand is missing \Nsome suit of eight or "pa" tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.97,0:20:51.22,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you get when you put them together?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.49,0:20:53.51,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,He needs...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.51,0:20:54.55,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,"Pei" and "pa"...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.27,0:20:57.34,DCMain,BOTH,0000,0000,0000,,He wants toilet paper!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.34,0:20:58.93,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.93,0:21:03.40,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,Dad was embarrassed Yoko-chan would \Nlearn he was out of toilet paper,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.40,0:21:05.10,DCMain,RAN,0000,0000,0000,,so he wrote it as a code.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.10,0:21:06.24,DCMain,YOKO,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.66,0:21:14.12,DCItalic,KOGORO,0000,0000,0000,,Paper... please!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:39.96,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, you said that code was \Neasily deciphered by a kid,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.48,0:22:46.90,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,but this one seems way \Ntougher to crack to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.90,0:22:48.47,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.67,0:22:52.54,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it sure does make you curious
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.04,0:22:54.97,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,when something isn't where \Nit's supposed to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.90,0:22:58.43,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,For example...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.73,0:23:02.98,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Like a shogi piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.41,0:23:05.98,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.40,0:23:08.32,DCMain,WAKITA,0000,0000,0000,,Wouldn't that make you curious?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.68,0:23:10.48,DCMain,CONAN,0000,0000,0000,,Not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.99,0:23:15.49,Poirot,SIGN,0000,0000,0000,,Poirot
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.05,0:23:15.49,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Amuro-san, you're looking \Nat that photo again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.27,0:23:18.37,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Is that your girlfriend?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.26,0:23:20.12,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.86,0:23:23.89,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,We've got orders piling up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.89,0:23:25.57,DCMain,AZUSA,0000,0000,0000,,Could you do your job, please?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.10,0:23:26.92,DCMain,AMURO,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
